rings, earing, mask, neck item to get. Str sits about 171 with items and I know AC is king. Suggestions, like I already don't have a good idea, but Im wondering what I can get without taking massive time and money from my main to outfit my warrior. Thanks for the input. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujontann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jontann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#CC9900>(10/26/00 11:43:53 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.europa.com/~jmb/images/JonIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: TROLL WARRIOR</span><hr size=1> If you can afford black sapphire earrings (the AC 5 ones, I don't remember which metal they use), I'd probably go that route.  If not, I'm wearing Gold Topaz (AC 3 and some disease save) because they're cheap and have good AC.  My first choice for rings would be plat fire wedding rings, with jagged bands as a second choice (both are AC 5 but the HPs on the plat fire rings is more useful than the str, IMHO.)  Neck and face are tougher slots.  I'd probably get one of those new 9 AC player made neck pieces (smithing) and then maybe just a dented brass mask or some such.<br>
